headline: Is Camden’s New US$600 Million Buyback and Dividend Hike Altering The Investment Case For CPT?
summary: Earlier this month, Camden Property Trust reported fourth-quarter 2025 and full-year results showing higher sales and net income, raised its quarterly dividend to US$1.06 per share, and received Board approval for a new US$600 million share repurchase authorization. The company also issued 2026 earnings and funds-from-operations guidance while recording a US$12,916,000 impairment on land development, underscoring a refocus toward higher-demand Sunbelt assets and capital returns.
